history.content:
See @5644: first-hand info from the professor.

--

I took the class last semester, the prerequisites are not strictly enforced or required. 

61AB are pretty much required, or a really strong programming background (there will be functional programming involved for the labs, http://lbstanza.org/ )

Everything beyond that are just recommendations for things that can influence your final project to make it tailored to something you have prior experience with. But with a little effort, you can find a topic of interest and excel on your project even without prior knowledge.
